# Bracketed `[ key-term ]` selectors (spec/grammar.md:109-111). Every key-term form parses:
# a number (including a negative literal), a bare identifier (a literal word key), a `:name` read,
# a word literal, and a parenthesized expression — plus a chain that interleaves a selector with
# dotted fields.
print :nums[1]
print :nums[-1]
print :ages[tom]
print :ages[:who]
print :ages["tom"]
print :nums[(:i + 1)]
print :a.b[1].c
